The paper deals with video compression using neural networks to predict saliency information, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses data management and storage systems, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, which could be related to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
